 "faq": [
  {
   "question": "Where does Protection Paladin Phase 5 BiS come from?",
   "answer": "From the gear worn by 211 top-ranked Protection Paladin DPS parses on Warcraft Logs during Phase 5 (Sunwell Plateau), aggregated per slot — what high parsers actually equip, not a spreadsheet ideal."
  },
  {
   "question": "What are the highest-consensus Protection Paladin items in Phase 5?",
   "answer": "Lightbringer Wristguards (91%), Lightbringer Waistguard (88%), Lightbringer Handguards (86%). When an item sits above ~70% among top parsers, treat it as the priority drop to chase."
  },
  {
   "question": "Should I follow this list exactly for Phase 5?",
   "answer": "Use it as a loot-priority guide, not a checklist — expand each slot's alternatives, because second-choice items are often within a few percent and drop from entirely different bosses in Sunwell Plateau."
  },
  {
   "question": "What gems should a Protection Paladin use in Phase 5?",
   "answer": "Powerful Earthstorm Diamond in the meta socket, then Solid Empyrean Sapphire and Glowing Shadowsong Amethyst in the coloured sockets. Phase 5 is where the epic gems from Sunwell replace their rare equivalents — that swap alone is worth several item levels across a full set."
  },
  {
   "question": "What enchants does a Protection Paladin need in Phase 5?",
   "answer": "11 slots are worth enchanting. The biggest swings are Glyph of Power on head, Greater Inscription of Warding on shoulders, Nethercleft Leg Armor on legs and Enchant Weapon - Major Spellpower on main hand. The head and shoulder enchants are consumable items rather than enchanter work — Glyph of Power comes from Almaador — Shattrath City."
  }
 ]
